{"schemaVersion":{"patch":0,"minor":3,"major":0},"abstract":[{"text":"A modification that uses CCDIK to manipulate a series of bones to reach a target in 2D.","type":"text"}],"primaryContentSections":[{"kind":"declarations","declarations":[{"languages":["swift"],"tokens":[{"kind":"keyword","text":"class"},{"text":" ","kind":"text"},{"kind":"identifier","text":"SkeletonModification2DCCDIK"}],"platforms":["macOS"]}]},{"content":[{"type":"heading","text":"Overview","level":2,"anchor":"overview"},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"text":"This ","type":"text"},{"type":"reference","identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/SkeletonModification2D","isActive":true},{"type":"text","text":" uses an algorithm called Cyclic Coordinate Descent Inverse Kinematics, or CCDIK, to manipulate a chain of bones in a "},{"type":"reference","isActive":true,"identifier":"doc:\/\/SwiftGodot\/documentation\/SwiftGodot\/Skeleton2D"},{"text":" so it reaches a defined target.","type":"text"}]},{"type":"paragraph","inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"CCDIK works by rotating a set of bones, typically called a “bone chain”, on a single axis. Each bone is rotated to face the target from the tip (by default), which over a chain of bones allow it to rotate properly to reach the target. Because the bones only rotate on a single axis, CCDIK "},{"inlineContent":[{"type":"text","text":"can"}],"type":"emphasis"},{"type":"text","text":" look more robotic than other IK solvers."}]},{"style":"note","type":"aside","name":"Note","content":[{"inlineContent":[{"text":"The CCDIK modifier has ","type":"text"},{"type":"codeVoice","code":"ccdik_joints"},{"type":"text","text":", which are the data objects that hold the data for each joint in the CCDIK chain. This is different from a bone! CCDIK joints hold the data needed for each bone in the bone chain used by CCDIK."}],"type":"paragraph"}]},{"inlineContent":[{"text":"CCDIK also fully supports angle constraints, allowing for more control ove